rComments: His lectures are very clear and helps you actually understand what you are learning. Back in ANP1107, I really struggled with the renal section but in PHS4300 with the help of prof Kennedy, I was able to easily grasp the content and even enjoy what I was learning about!

you must attend the lecture/listen to recording as his powerpoints have no words. Questions were fair, doesnt over complicate them like savory. does not use the book. do his practice Qs and take good notes and you should be good for the finals.

Kennedy was just an average prof to me. Content was seemingly less than other professors (although his PPTs are significantly more lengthy) - the sample exam questions he provided were really tough for me, but the ones he provided on the midterm were very decent.

He seems very nice, and he'll tell you that this and that won't be on the exam - but it will be, so don't skip anything when studying for his midterm! Helped me understand some concepts I didn't have a good grasp on in ANP1107. Provides practice questions, and couple of them were on the actual midterm - bonus!

you need to attend class because he gives additional information with the slides but hes an amazing prof. He makes everything super simple for students to understand and doesn't overwhelm you with information. His exam questions are fair and usually about things he  mentioned in class that were important! Great prof, would definitely recommend!
Very clear, well spoken, makes it interesting. Would recommend.
